import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    data['date'] = data['date'].dt.to_period('M')

    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='date', y='rate', hue='series', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the overall trend of unemployment rate across all industries from 2000 to 2010?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(title='Industry', loc='upper left')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    data_2010 = data[data['year'] == 2010]
    industry_rate = data_2010.groupby('series')['rate'].mean().reset_index()
    industry_rate = industry_rate.sort_values('rate', ascending=False)
    max_rate = industry_rate['rate'].max()

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax = sns.barplot(x='series', y='rate', data=industry_rate, palette='viridis')
    plt.axhline(y=max_rate, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Highest Rate: {max_rate:.2f}')
    plt.title('Which industry had the highest unemployment rate in 2010?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Industry')
    plt.ylabel('Unemployment Rate')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    data['month'] = data['date'].dt.month

    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    ax = sns.boxplot(x='month', y='rate', data=data)
    plt.title('How does the unemployment rate vary across different months of the year?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Month')
    plt.ylabel('Unemployment Rate')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
